data.body:
Partially overhauled the Guide for iOS 6+ Game Center functionality.
#### Encapsulated repetitious code into single-purpose methods

Instead of this type code being repeated all over the file:

``` c#
if (_window != null)
{
    if(viewController == null)
    {
        viewController = new GuideViewController(_gameViewController);
        _window.Add(viewController.View);
        viewController.View.Hidden = true;
    }

    prevGestures=TouchPanel.EnabledGestures;
    TouchPanel.EnabledGestures=GestureType.None;
    viewController.PresentModalViewController(leaderboardController, true);
    IsVisible = true;
}
```

Everything for showing and hiding Game Center view controllers is now encapsulated into two reusable and easily testable methods, which correctly handle the different modes of presenting/dismissing controllers for iOS 5 vs. iOS 6+:

``` c#
private static void ShowViewController(UIViewController viewController)
{
    // ...
}

private static void HideViewController(UIViewController viewController)
{
    // ...
}
```
#### Fixed runtime warnings for Game Center in iOS 7

Using a separate `GuideViewController` as a parent for Game Center view controllers generates runtime warnings in iOS 7. The new "correct" way to open Game Center view controllers (for iOS 6+) is to simply open them with the root view controller (as seen in the new `ShowViewController` method mentioned above).
#### iOS 6+ no longer uses deprecated methods to open Game Center windows

Instead of using the deprecated `GKLeaderboardViewController` and `GKAchievementViewController`, iOS 6+ now uses the new `GKGameCenterViewController` for showing leaderboards and achievements. As with everything else, the old methods are still in place for iOS 5 and older. Related note: All compiler warnings in Guide.cs have been fixed.
#### Fixed a MatchMaker crash bug

Setting playersToInvite to null caused the game to crash, so now we pass in an empty array instead which seems to work well (tested on iOS 5+).
#### Fixed the file formatting

Tabs, spaces, braces in Guide.cs have been fixed to be in line with MonoGame's coding conventions.
#### Bonus feature: Twitter

Added access to iOS's Twitter API in the Guide now too.
